500:When could have I possibly gone outside?\n;When could it have possibly turned to day?\p;
600:With the last earthquake, I had been out for more than an hour.\n;“Maybe this time, I had been unconscious for the entire night,” I thought to myself.\p;
700:I remembered the earthquake's tremendous impact.\n;Yet another illusive feeling hit me... like the tremors were resonating with the very blood coursing through my veins, threatening to burst open from the inside.\p;
800:Maybe... Maybe this was Heaven?\n;Maybe I'd died in that earthquake.\p;
900:...“Heaven,” huh?\n;There was no way an otaku freak like me would go to Heaven.\p;
1000:That wasn't even mentioning how I hadn't even been able to save my own little sister.\n;How I'd been the worst possible brother to her.\n;How I'd made Rimi kill Sena and Kozupii.\p;
1100:Hell would be a far more fitting place for someone like me.\n;Although, obviously I'd choose Heaven if I could.\p;
1200:My body didn't feel quite right.\n;I was being overwhelmed by a sensation of... walking on top of a fluffy cloud.\n;I couldn't quite understand it.\p;
1300:But regardless of how I felt, I forced myself to get up.\p;
1400:The feeling of being rocked by the waves hadn't simply been my imagination after all.\n;This was a world with a neverending surface of crystal-clear water.\n;A world where, no matter where I looked, blue filled my view.\p;
1500:And I had been right in the middle of it, lying down.\p;
1600:Where was I?\p;
1700:Was this really Heaven?\p;
1800:But... I felt like I'd seen this scenery before...\p;
1900:〔Rimi〕“That sky... Where is it?”\p;
2000:A voice resounded within my mind.\n;A voice which rose from the depths of my memories.\p;
2100:Right... I remembered now. I'd seen it in a dream before.\n;Rimi had been there.\n;I had talked to her as she looked up at the blue sky, her face clearly one of holding back tears.\p;
2200:Was I seeing the same dream as I had back then?\p;
2300:But... no matter where I looked, there was no one other than me.\p;
2400:There was no one here.\n;Not even Rimi.\n;It was far too reposeful.\p;
