2800:Sound was a series of vibrations.\n;And those vibrations, in turn, created waves.\p;
2900:Among those waves, just like I had been a few moments ago, there was someone lying down.\p;
3000:I stood up.\n;My field of view expanded.\p;
3100:The one drifting along the waves... was Rimi.\p;
3200:She was so unbelievably pale, she appeared as if she was dead.\n;Her eyes were closed, and both of her hands were resting gently on her chest.\p;
3300:And she simply stayed that way—facing up to the sky, not moving even a single inch.\p;
3400:<i>R</i><i>i</i><i>m</i><i>i</i><i>,</i> <i>w</i><i>a</i><i>k</i><i>e</i> <i>u</i><i>p</i><i>.</i>\p;
3500:Even though I called out to her, she didn't react.\n;She was dead.\n;I knew that for certain.\p;
3600:But it wasn't just her.\n;The world itself... was dead.\p;
3700:And so I just stood there, not knowing what to do.\p;
3800:Right at that very moment, Rimi's prone body gradually sank beneath the surface of water.\n;As soon as I realized what was happening, she was already completely submerged.\p;
3900:“How was I standing on top of water at all?” I wondered.\n;Curious, I fixed my gazed below the water's surface.\p;
4000:Beyond it, there was only darkness.\n;The sky was so bright, and yet... even though the water was so clear...\p;
4100:...below it, there was only an eternal darkness that seemed to swallow all.\n;And Rimi, still lying on her back, was slowly sinking farther and farther into its depths.\p;
4200:I had to go after her.\n;I needed to wake her up.\p;
4300:But as soon as that thought crossed my mind... even though I had been able to stand on water until then... all support suddenly disappeared out from under me.\p;
4400:I sank.\n;My body grew heavier with each passing second.\p;
4500:It was like I was underwater.\n;But it wasn't as though I couldn't breathe.\p;
4600:The water was very warm, too.\n;I just wanted to drift within this comfortable sensation for all eternity.\n;That was the way it made me feel.\p;
4700:If I had to give an example... rather than ocean water, it was more like amniotic fluid.\n;This very well might have been how a fetus felt inside its mother's womb.\p;
4800:I thought the darkness continued forever, but in truth, there was a bottom to it.\n;It was so dark, I couldn't even see my feet.\n;I simply felt an odd, sticky sensation on my soles.\p;
4900:I stood in the middle of the darkness.\p;
5000:When I looked up, I found I could no longer see the surface.\n;That blue sky, too, had been veiled completely by the darkness.\p;
5100:The sole source of light was a single ray that descended down from above like a thin thread.\n;Much like a spotlight would, it pointed to a single place.\p;
5200:And yet, unlike a spotlight, there was nothing beneath it to be illuminated.\n;It only lit up a meaningless spot.\p;
5300:Nervously, I stepped into the light.\p;
5400:It was ever so faint and gentle, but the moment I bathed in it, my chest began to ache.\n;What was this sensation?\p;
5500:It felt almost as if I could cry at a moment's notice.\n;As if my heart itself was being rended.\n;That was the sensation that overtook me.\p;
5600:Where could Rimi be right now after sinking all the way down here?\n;Relying on the faint light source alone, I made my way out from beneath the spot of light, then searched the darkness.\p;
5700:Soon, my toes hit something soft and yielding.\n;I kneeled down, and this time, tried touching it with my hand.\n;What I felt was so cold, it was capable of freezing my very fingertips.\p;
5800:Little by little, my eyes adjusted to the darkness.\n;And before long, I realized something.\p;
5900:I was touching a person.\n;A person, lying collapsed on the ground.\n;Rimi.\p;
